/**********************************************
 * Info
 * ==================================
 * Array of information -> with type Job, Education and Certification
 ***********************************************/
export const resumes = [
  {
    id: 1,
    institution: "Xccelerate",
    title: "Software Engineer Instructor",
    date: "2020-2021",
    type: "Job",
    description:
      "I taught software engineering over the course of a year, enabling students to build their own fullstack applications, which were typically deployed on AWS.",
    image: "",
  },
  {
    id: 2,
    institution: "University of Helsinki",
    title: "Software Engineer Teaching Assistant",
    date: "Spring 2019",
    type: "Education",
    description:
      "This course taught me the basics of the Java programming language and core Object-Oriented Programming concepts. The course is the first of a two semester line of classes from the University of Helsinki, Finland's computer science degree program. This, combined with the second part of the course, is the first year of computer science classes for CS majors.",
    image: "",
  },
  {
    id: 3,
    institution: "Microsoft",
    title: "Microsoft Javascript Certification",
    type: "Certification",
    date: "Spring 2019",
    description:
      "This course taught me how to develop prototypes in Javascript and Node.js. I also began learning the basics of back-end development. This certification contains three courses: Building Interactive Prototypes Using JavaScript, Building Functional Prototypes using Node.js and Designing a Technical Solution.",
    image: "",
  },
  {
    id: 4,
    institution: "Free Code Camp",
    title: "Front End Certifications",
    type: "Certification",
    date: "Spring 2019",
    description:
      "I completed the first three certifications, each requiring around 300 hours of practice. These certifications (Responsive Web Design, Front End Libraries Certifications and Javascript Algorithms & Data Structures) gave me a broad overview of various tools, such as React, Redux and jQuery.",
    image: "",
  },
  {
    id: 5,
    institution: "General Assembly",
    title: "Illustrator and Photoshop Bootcamp",
    type: "Certification",
    date: "Spring 2019",
    description: "",
    image: "",
  },
  {
    id: 6,
    institution: "University of Helsinki",
    title: "Illustrator and Photoshop Bootcamp",
    type: "Certification",
    date: "Spring 2019",
    description:
      "This course serves as an introduction to modern web application development with JavaScript. The main focus is on building single page applications with ReactJS that use REST APIs built with Node.js. The course also contains a section on GraphQL, a modern alternative to REST APIs (still in progress).",
